Sentencas: Fuel cells with BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3d (BZCY) proton-conducting electrolyte is fabricated using spray-modified pressing method.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: In the present study the spray-modified pressing technology is developed to prepare thin electrolyte layers on porous Ni-BZCY anode supports.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: SEM data show the BZCY electrolyte film is uniform and dense, well-bonded with the anode substrate.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: An anode-supported fuel cell with BZCY electrolyte and Ba0.5Sr0.5Co0.8Fe0.2O3d (BSCF) cathode is characterized from 600 to 700 degrees C using hydrogen as fuel and ambient air as oxidant.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: Maximum power density of 536 mW cm2 along with a 1.01 V OCV at 700 degrees C is obtained.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: Impedance spectra show that Ohmic resistances contribute minor parts to the total ones, for instance, only similar to 23% when operating at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method

Sentencas: The results demonstrate that spray-modified pressing technology offers a simple and effective way to fabricate quality electrolyte film suitable to operate in intermediate temperature.
Titulo: A Performance Study of Solid Oxide Fuel Cells With BaZr0.1Ce0.7Y0.2O3-d Electrolyte Developed by Spray-Modified Pressing Method
